Colour . Pale green in life (
Fig. 1
), thorax of some specimens with a darker green circular mark on metepisternum. Cells of tegmina each with a prominent darker green spot or not. Legs light green. Beaded area of ventral lobe of pronotum and occiputal carina and adjacent gena yellow.

Song. The song of this species is a continuous chirp uttered after dark. Each chirp consists of two pulses (
Fig. 7
).

Colour . In life pale green, with yellow as indicated (
Fig. 2 A
